# Blockchain-Based Voting System — Technical Specification

> **Project Type:** College Mini-Project  
> **Date:** March 2026  
> **Stack:** Next.js · Solidity · Ethereum (Ganache) · MongoDB · Web3.js

---

## 1. Overview

### 1.1 Purpose

This application is a **decentralized, blockchain-based voting system** designed for college elections. It replaces paper/manual voting with a tamper-proof, transparent, and verifiable digital process. Every vote is recorded as a transaction on an Ethereum blockchain, making it immutable and publicly auditable.

### 1.2 Core Functionality

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Student Registration** | Students register with personal details, a password, and a simulated fingerprint hash. |
| **Admin Dashboard** | Admins create/manage elections, add candidates, and publish results. |
| **Biometric Verification** | A SHA-256 fingerprint hash is stored and verified before each vote to confirm identity. |
| **Blockchain Voting** | Votes are cast via an Ethereum smart contract, preventing double-voting at the protocol level. |
| **Result Publication** | Admins publish results; students view tallied results on their dashboard. |

### 1.3 Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | **Next.js 14** (App Router) | Server-side rendering, routing, API routes |
| Smart Contracts | **Solidity ^0.8.x** | Voting logic, double-vote prevention |
| Blockchain | **Ganache** (local) | Local Ethereum test network |
| Contract Tooling | **Hardhat** | Compilation, deployment, testing of contracts |
| Database | **MongoDB** (via Mongoose) | Student data, candidate data, fingerprint hashes |
| Auth | **bcrypt** + **JWT** | Password hashing, session tokens |
| Blockchain Lib | **Web3.js** or **ethers.js** | Frontend ↔ smart contract interaction |
| Fingerprint Sim | **SHA-256** (crypto module) | Simulated biometric hash |

