## 2. Database Architecture

All non-blockchain data is stored in **MongoDB**. Three primary collections are used.

### 2.1 Collection: `students`

Stores registered student information and authentication credentials.

```js
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  fullName: String,             // e.g. "Ansh Mehta"
  email: String,                // unique, indexed — e.g. "ansh@college.edu"
  studentId: String,            // unique, indexed — e.g. "21CS045"
  department: String,           // e.g. "Computer Science"
  year: Number,                 // e.g. 3
  passwordHash: String,         // bcrypt hash (12 salt rounds)
  walletAddress: String,        // Ethereum address assigned from Ganache
  role: { type: String, default: "student" },
  isApproved: { type: Boolean, default: false },
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}
```

**Indexes:** `{ email: 1 }` (unique), `{ studentId: 1 }` (unique)

### 2.2 Collection: `candidates`

Stores candidate details linked to a specific election.

```js
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  fullName: String,             // e.g. "Priya Sharma"
  party: String,                // e.g. "Student Progress Alliance"
  department: String,           // e.g. "Electronics"
  electionId: ObjectId,         // references the election this candidate belongs to
  manifesto: String,            // short manifesto text (max 500 chars)
  photoUrl: String,             // path to candidate photo (optional)
  candidateIndex: Number,       // index in the smart contract's candidate array
  createdAt: Date
}
```

**Index:** `{ electionId: 1 }`

### 2.3 Collection: `fingerprints`

Stores simulated fingerprint hashes for biometric verification.

```js
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  studentId: String,            // references students.studentId
  fingerprintHash: String,      // SHA-256 hash of the simulated fingerprint data
  createdAt: Date
}
```

**Index:** `{ studentId: 1 }` (unique)

> [!NOTE]
> The fingerprint hash is generated during registration by hashing a student-provided passphrase (simulating a biometric scan) with Node.js `crypto.createHash('sha256')`. In a production system, this would be replaced with actual biometric sensor integration.

### 2.4 Additional Collection: `elections`

Stores election metadata (the actual votes live on-chain).

```js
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  title: String,                // e.g. "Student Council Election 2026"
  description: String,
  contractAddress: String,      // deployed smart contract address
  status: {                     // "upcoming" | "active" | "completed" | "results_published"
    type: String,
    enum: ["upcoming", "active", "completed", "results_published"],
    default: "upcoming"
  },
  startDate: Date,
  endDate: Date,
  createdBy: ObjectId,          // admin user ID
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}
```

### 2.5 Collection: `admins`

```js
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  username: String,             // unique
  email: String,                // unique
  passwordHash: String,         // bcrypt hash
  role: { type: String, default: "admin" },
  createdAt: Date
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Admin registration requires a **server-side secret key** (`ADMIN_SECRET_KEY` in `.env`). This prevents unauthorized users from creating admin accounts.

