## 5. Election Management

### 5.1 Create Election (Admin Only)

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/elections/create`

**Flow:**
1. Admin fills form: title, description, start date, end date
2. API creates election record in MongoDB with `status: "upcoming"`
3. A new `Voting` smart contract is deployed to Ganache via Hardhat
4. The deployed contract address is saved to the election record

### 5.2 Add Candidates to Election

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/elections/:electionId/candidates`

**Flow:**
1. Admin adds candidate name, party, department, manifesto
2. Candidate is added to the smart contract via `addCandidate(name)`
3. Candidate record is saved in MongoDB with the `candidateIndex` from the contract

### 5.3 Election Status Lifecycle

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Upcoming: Admin creates election
    Upcoming --> Active: Admin starts election\n(startDate reached)
    Active --> Completed: Admin ends election\n(endDate reached or manual)
    Completed --> ResultsPublished: Admin publishes results
    ResultsPublished --> [*]
```

| Status | Student Actions Allowed | Admin Actions Allowed |
|---|---|---|
| `upcoming` | View election details | Add candidates, edit details |
| `active` | Cast vote | Monitor live vote count |
| `completed` | Wait for results | Publish results |
| `results_published` | View results | View results |

### 5.4 View Elections

**Endpoint:** `GET /api/elections`

Returns all elections with optional query filters:
- `?status=active` — only active elections
- `?status=results_published` — elections with published results

