## 10. Security Considerations

### 10.1 Authentication & Session Security

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Password storage | bcrypt with **12 salt rounds** — never store plaintext |
| JWT security | Store in `httpOnly`, `secure`, `sameSite: strict` cookies |
| Token expiry | 24-hour expiration; refresh on active use |
| Admin registration | Protected by server-side secret key |
| Route protection | Next.js middleware checks JWT on every protected route |

### 10.2 Blockchain Security

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Double voting | `hasVoted` mapping in smart contract — reverts duplicate transactions |
| Unauthorized actions | `onlyAdmin` modifier on sensitive functions |
| Contract tampering | Once deployed, contract code is immutable on-chain |
| Private key exposure | Keys stored server-side in environment variables, never exposed to frontend |

### 10.3 Database Security

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Injection attacks | Mongoose ODM parameterizes all queries — no raw string concatenation |
| Data validation | Schema-level validation with Mongoose + API-level validation with `zod` or `joi` |
| Connection security | Use `MONGODB_URI` from `.env` — never hardcode credentials |
| Fingerprint data | Only the SHA-256 hash is stored — the original passphrase is never persisted |

### 10.4 API Security

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| CORS | Restrict to known origins (`http://localhost:3000` in development) |
| Rate limiting | Use `express-rate-limit` middleware on auth endpoints (max 5 attempts/minute) |
| Input sanitization | Validate and sanitize all inputs before processing |
| Error handling | Never expose stack traces or internal errors to the client |

### 10.5 Environment Variables

```env
# .env.local
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/voting-system
JWT_SECRET=your-256-bit-secret
ADMIN_SECRET_KEY=your-admin-registration-secret
GANACHE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:7545
NEXT_PUBLIC_GANACHE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:7545
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **Never commit `.env.local` to version control.** Add it to `.gitignore` immediately.

